XPath: /p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14216" identifier="8186c46264e4391f37cea49e4012f05d">
        <source>Note: To make a negative number positive you can take its absolute value.</source>
        <target>crwdns14216:0crwdne14216:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14217" identifier="447c4f0eabd0939a694c317b05cc898f">
        <source>For example the absolute value of -9 is +9 and the absolute value of +9 is +9.</source>
        <target>crwdns14217:0crwdne14217:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14218" identifier="b994d7c40d7de4c2cf6bb191a0fb81d0">
        <source>That is &lt;code&gt;scratch:[abs v] of (-9) // 9&lt;/code&gt;.</source>
        <target>crwdns14218:0crwdne14218:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14219" identifier="cb6382e35d706ff7ca082402c8b08d3a">
        <source>To return an absolute value of a number in Scratch, choose the “abs” function from the drop down menu of &lt;code&gt;scratch:[sqrt v] of ()&lt;/code&gt; block under the “operators” scripts.</source>
        <target>crwdns14219:0crwdne14219:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
